        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> All nerfage sucks of course but the CoS was/is pretty overpowered.  I play on TZ so I know how valuable this little item is.  I think everyones mentioned that you lose your target if you don't have see invis on.  Well, imagine a SK jousting you and hitting his CoS after every hit.  You are dead if you don't have see invis.  Period.  A necro hitting the CoS right after the dots hit ... very powerful item.  Or so Verant would have us think!</P><P>In my world this item really has minimal pvp value.  With the amount of see invis items available nowadays, I can't remember the last person I fought that did not have see invis.  People on pvp servers are not stupid.  If you are getting your ass kicked because you can't see invis, well you damn well get an item that gives it.  So the pvp arguement is crap.  Verant just used that excuse to nerf it.  They nerfed it becuase of its pve powers not pvp.  I won't bother listing them as lots of others here have already done that.</P><P>I would never give my pre-nerf one up tho, and I seriously would probably quit if they did retro nerf mine.  It IS the most valuable item you can have in pve next to Epic/Zland and possibly Beads.</P><P><p><font face="Arial" color="#ff9900" font size="2"><p </P><P>align="center"><strong>Retrievil Hesevil<br><BR>'If you have a problem, if no one else can help, and if you can<BR>find him,<br><BR>maybe you can hire... The Evil One.'<br><BR>-Tallon Zek -<br><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
